          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is $135 worth it for a serum?",
            "answer": "Most serums use the same 10 ingredients. Amrutini® Luminosity Dewdrops use four undiscovered regional ingredients — sourced from the rarest corners of India, bio-engineered in New York City. No other Western skincare brand uses Liquefied Gold Muga Silk or Full-Moon Silver Tips Imperial Tea. The clinical results speak for themselves: 100% of participants saw improved radiance in 28 days."
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is it suitable for sensitive skin?",
            "answer": "Yes. The formula is free from parabens, sulfates, synthetic fragrances, and harsh chemicals. It's been dermatologist-tested and is suitable for all skin types including sensitive skin. The Hibiscus-derived AHAs are gentle precision exfoliants — not harsh chemical peels."
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What's different from other serums?",
            "answer": "Four things no other Western brand uses: Liquefied Gold Muga Silk (surgical-grade regenerative), Silver Tips Imperial Tea (full-moon harvested, polyphenol-dense), Tremella Mushroom (500x moisture retention), and Ashwagandha Root Extract (cortisol-neutralizing). Combined with clinical-grade Niacinamide and Sodium Hyaluronate, this is a formula unlike anything in Western skincare."
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How fast do results show?",
            "answer": "In our 28-day clinical trial, 100% of participants saw improved skin radiance, and 94% reported visibly smoother skin. Most customers notice a dewy, glass-like glow within the first week. Full results — firmer, tighter, more luminous skin — appear at 4 weeks."
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What are the Silk Cocoons?",
            "answer": "The Silk Cocoons are precision micro-exfoliation tools made from real silk. Each cocoon is used wet to gently buff skin before applying the Dewdrops, allowing the serum to penetrate deeper. Each cocoon lasts 3–4 uses, and 4 cocoons are included free with every order — a $48 value."
          }
        }
